Rainy conditions are expected to persist on Monday in Gauteng, North West and Mpumalanga with the Weather Service also predicting widespread showers and thundershowers into Tuesday. The Service on Sunday issued a warning for possible flooding with some parts of the North West and Gauteng as soaking rains continued. Forecaster, Mbavhi Maliage says, “We have issued out a watch for possible flooding over the province. The rainfall is expected to continue up until Tuesday evening, and then on Wednesday the rain would’ve subsided by then… so Wednesday and Thursday, this type of rainfall is not expected over the province of Gauteng.” Click link below for more on the story:   